  "description": "<i>Math Mission</i> is a 1-player math learning game for the 8-bit Atari computer.<br><br>The player must answer math questions as their spaceship flies cross an alien landscape at the bottom of the screen.  The player has a limited fuel supply which can only be replenished by quickly answering math questions correctly.  Wrong answers and slow answers cause fuel drainage.  The players receives a bonus for answering certain numbers of questions correctly, and for successfully completing a number of worlds.  As the game progresses, math challenges become more difficult.  If the ship runs out of fuel, it's game over. ",
